Invalid Customer Test

Since customerId is now a String, there is no UUID conversion anymore.

So this test:

customerId = "invalid-uuid"

is no longer meaningful and should be removed.

Instead create:

@Test
@WithMockOflUser(role = "ADVSHIP_ADMIN")
void testGetFedexSubscription_EmptyCustomerId() throws Exception {

    mockMvc.perform(
                    get("/v1/api/fedex/subscription")
                            .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)
                            .with(csrf())
                            .header("Authorization", "dummy-token")
                            .param("customerId", "")
                            .param("accountNumber", "ACC1001"))
            .andExpect(status().isBadRequest());
}

Only keep this test if your controller has validation like:

@RequestParam
@NotBlank
String customerId

Otherwise remove the third controller test entirely.

Important

Now that IDs are Strings, update:

FedexSubscriptionProjection
FedexSubscriptionResponse
Entity
Repository
Service Interface
Service Impl
Controller
Tests

to use String consistently. Any remaining UUID in the chain will likely cause compilation failures.